3430 case TIM_CHANNEL_1:
3431 {
3432 TIM_CCxChannelCmd(htim->Instance, TIM_CHANNEL_1, TIM_CCx_ENABLE);
3433 __HAL_TIM_ENABLE_IT(htim, TIM_IT_CC1);
3434 break;
3435 }
3436
3437 case TIM_CHANNEL_2:
3438 {
3439 TIM_CCxChannelCmd(htim->Instance, TIM_CHANNEL_2, TIM_CCx_ENABLE);
3440 __HAL_TIM_ENABLE_IT(htim, TIM_IT_CC2);
3441 break;
3442 }
3443
3444 default :
3445 {
3446 TIM_CCxChannelCmd(htim->Instance, TIM_CHANNEL_1, TIM_CCx_ENABLE);
3447 TIM_CCxChannelCmd(htim->Instance, TIM_CHANNEL_2, TIM_CCx_ENABLE);
3448 __HAL_TIM_ENABLE_IT(htim, TIM_IT_CC1);
3449 __HAL_TIM_ENABLE_IT(htim, TIM_IT_CC2);
3450 break;
3451 }
3452 }
3453
3454 /* Enable the Peripheral */
3455 __HAL_TIM_ENABLE(htim);
3456
3457 /* Return function status */
3458 return HAL_OK;
3459}
3460
3471HAL_StatusTypeDef HAL_TIM_Encoder_Stop_IT(TIM_HandleTypeDef *htim, uint32_t Channel)
3472{
3473 /* Check the parameters */
3474 assert_param(IS_TIM_ENCODER_INTERFACE_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
3475
3476 /* Disable the Input Capture channels 1 and 2
3477 (in the EncoderInterface the two possible channels that can be used are TIM_CHANNEL_1 and TIM_CHANNEL_2) */
3478 if (Channel == TIM_CHANNEL_1)
3479 {
3480 TIM_CCxChannelCmd(htim->Instance, TIM_CHANNEL_1, TIM_CCx_DISABLE);
3481
3482 /* Disable the capture compare Interrupts 1 */
3483 __HAL_TIM_DISABLE_IT(htim, TIM_IT_CC1);
3484 }
3485 else if (Channel == TIM_CHANNEL_2)
3486 {
3487 TIM_CCxChannelCmd(htim->Instance, TIM_CHANNEL_2, TIM_CCx_DISABLE);
3488
3489 /* Disable the capture compare Interrupts 2 */
3490 __HAL_TIM_DISABLE_IT(htim, TIM_IT_CC2);
3491 }
3492 else
3493 {
3494 TIM_CCxChannelCmd(htim->Instance, TIM_CHANNEL_1, TIM_CCx_DISABLE);
3495 TIM_CCxChannelCmd(htim->Instance, TIM_CHANNEL_2, TIM_CCx_DISABLE);
3496
3497 /* Disable the capture compare Interrupts 1 and 2 */
3498 __HAL_TIM_DISABLE_IT(htim, TIM_IT_CC1);
3499 __HAL_TIM_DISABLE_IT(htim, TIM_IT_CC2);
3500 }
3501
3502 /* Disable the Peripheral */
3503 __HAL_TIM_DISABLE(htim);
3504
3505 /* Set the TIM channel(s) state */
3506 if ((Channel == TIM_CHANNEL_1) || (Channel == TIM_CHANNEL_2))
3507 {
3508 TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_SET(htim, Channel, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY);
3509 TIM_CHANNEL_N_STATE_SET(htim, Channel, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY);
3510 }
3511 else
3512 {
3513 TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_1, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY);
3514 TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_2, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY);
3515 TIM_CHANNEL_N_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_1, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY);
3516 TIM_CHANNEL_N_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_2, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY);
3517 }
3518
3519 /* Return function status */
3520 return HAL_OK;
3521}
3522
3536HAL_StatusTypeDef HAL_TIM_Encoder_Start_DMA(TIM_HandleTypeDef *htim, uint32_t Channel, uint32_t *pData1,
3537 uint32_t *pData2, uint16_t Length)
3538{
3539 HAL_TIM_ChannelStateTypeDef channel_1_state = TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_GET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_1);
3540 HAL_TIM_ChannelStateTypeDef channel_2_state = TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_GET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_2);
3541 HAL_TIM_ChannelStateTypeDef complementary_channel_1_state = TIM_CHANNEL_N_STATE_GET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_1);
3542 HAL_TIM_ChannelStateTypeDef complementary_channel_2_state = TIM_CHANNEL_N_STATE_GET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_2);
3543
3544 /* Check the parameters */
3545 assert_param(IS_TIM_ENCODER_INTERFACE_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
3546
3547 /* Set the TIM channel(s) state */
3548 if (Channel == TIM_CHANNEL_1)
3549 {
3550 if ((channel_1_state == HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_BUSY)
3551 || (complementary_channel_1_state == HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_BUSY))
3552 {
3553 return HAL_BUSY;
3554 }
3555 else if ((channel_1_state == HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY)
3556 && (complementary_channel_1_state == HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY))
3557 {
3558 if ((pData1 == NULL) && (Length > 0U))
3559 {
3560 return HAL_ERROR;
3561 }
3562 else
3563 {
3564 TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_1, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_BUSY);
3565 TIM_CHANNEL_N_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_1, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_BUSY);
3566 }
3567 }
3568 else
3569 {
3570 return HAL_ERROR;
3571 }
3572 }
3573 else if (Channel == TIM_CHANNEL_2)
3574 {
3575 if ((channel_2_state == HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_BUSY)
3576 || (complementary_channel_2_state == HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_BUSY))
3577 {
3578 return HAL_BUSY;
3579 }
3580 else if ((channel_2_state == HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY)
3581 && (complementary_channel_2_state == HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY))
3582 {
3583 if ((pData2 == NULL) && (Length > 0U))
3584 {
3585 return HAL_ERROR;
3586 }
3587 else
3588 {
3589 TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_2, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_BUSY);
3590 TIM_CHANNEL_N_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_2, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_BUSY);
3591 }
3592 }
3593 else
3594 {
3595 return HAL_ERROR;
3596 }
3597 }
3598 else
3599 {
3600 if ((channel_1_state == HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_BUSY)
3601 || (channel_2_state == HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_BUSY)
3602 || (complementary_channel_1_state == HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_BUSY)
3603 || (complementary_channel_2_state == HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_BUSY))
3604 {
3605 return HAL_BUSY;
3606 }
3607 else if ((channel_1_state == HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY)
3608 && (channel_2_state == HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY)
3609 && (complementary_channel_1_state == HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY)
3610 && (complementary_channel_2_state == HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY))
3611 {
3612 if ((((pData1 == NULL) || (pData2 == NULL))) && (Length > 0U))
3613 {
3614 return HAL_ERROR;
3615 }
3616 else
3617 {
3618 TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_1, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_BUSY);
3619 TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_2, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_BUSY);
3620 TIM_CHANNEL_N_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_1, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_BUSY);
3621 TIM_CHANNEL_N_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_2, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_BUSY);
3622 }
3623 }
3624 else
3625 {
3626 return HAL_ERROR;
3627 }
3628 }
3629
3630 switch (Channel)
3631 {
3632 case TIM_CHANNEL_1:
3633 {
3634 /* Set the DMA capture callbacks */
3635 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC1]->XferCpltCallback = TIM_DMACaptureCplt;
3636 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC1]->XferHalfCpltCallback = TIM_DMACaptureHalfCplt;
3637
3638 /* Set the DMA error callback */
3639 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC1]->XferErrorCallback = TIM_DMAError ;
3640
3641 /* Enable the DMA channel */
3642 if (HAL_DMA_Start_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC1], (uint32_t)&htim->Instance->CCR1, (uint32_t)pData1,
3643 Length) != HAL_OK)
3644 {
3645 /* Return error status */
3646 return HAL_ERROR;
3647 }
3648 /* Enable the TIM Input Capture DMA request */
3649 __HAL_TIM_ENABLE_DMA(htim, TIM_DMA_CC1);
3650
3651 /* Enable the Capture compare channel */
3652 TIM_CCxChannelCmd(htim->Instance, TIM_CHANNEL_1, TIM_CCx_ENABLE);
3653
3654 /* Enable the Peripheral */
3655 __HAL_TIM_ENABLE(htim);
3656
3657 break;
3658 }
3659
3660 case TIM_CHANNEL_2:
3661 {
3662 /* Set the DMA capture callbacks */
3663 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC2]->XferCpltCallback = TIM_DMACaptureCplt;
3664 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC2]->XferHalfCpltCallback = TIM_DMACaptureHalfCplt;
3665
3666 /* Set the DMA error callback */
3667 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC2]->XferErrorCallback = TIM_DMAError;
3668 /* Enable the DMA channel */
3669 if (HAL_DMA_Start_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC2], (uint32_t)&htim->Instance->CCR2, (uint32_t)pData2,
3670 Length) != HAL_OK)
3671 {
3672 /* Return error status */
3673 return HAL_ERROR;
3674 }
3675 /* Enable the TIM Input Capture DMA request */
3676 __HAL_TIM_ENABLE_DMA(htim, TIM_DMA_CC2);
3677
3678 /* Enable the Capture compare channel */
3679 TIM_CCxChannelCmd(htim->Instance, TIM_CHANNEL_2, TIM_CCx_ENABLE);
3680
3681 /* Enable the Peripheral */
3682 __HAL_TIM_ENABLE(htim);
3683
3684 break;
3685 }
3686
3687 default:
3688 {
3689 /* Set the DMA capture callbacks */
3690 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC1]->XferCpltCallback = TIM_DMACaptureCplt;
3691 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC1]->XferHalfCpltCallback = TIM_DMACaptureHalfCplt;
3692
3693 /* Set the DMA error callback */
3694 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC1]->XferErrorCallback = TIM_DMAError ;
3695
3696 /* Enable the DMA channel */
3697 if (HAL_DMA_Start_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC1], (uint32_t)&htim->Instance->CCR1, (uint32_t)pData1,
3698 Length) != HAL_OK)
3699 {
3700 /* Return error status */
3701 return HAL_ERROR;
3702 }
3703
3704 /* Set the DMA capture callbacks */
3705 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC2]->XferCpltCallback = TIM_DMACaptureCplt;
3706 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC2]->XferHalfCpltCallback = TIM_DMACaptureHalfCplt;
3707
3708 /* Set the DMA error callback */
3709 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC2]->XferErrorCallback = TIM_DMAError ;
3710
3711 /* Enable the DMA channel */
3712 if (HAL_DMA_Start_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC2], (uint32_t)&htim->Instance->CCR2, (uint32_t)pData2,
3713 Length) != HAL_OK)
3714 {
3715 /* Return error status */
3716 return HAL_ERROR;
3717 }
3718
3719 /* Enable the TIM Input Capture DMA request */
3720 __HAL_TIM_ENABLE_DMA(htim, TIM_DMA_CC1);
3721 /* Enable the TIM Input Capture DMA request */
3722 __HAL_TIM_ENABLE_DMA(htim, TIM_DMA_CC2);
3723
3724 /* Enable the Capture compare channel */
3725 TIM_CCxChannelCmd(htim->Instance, TIM_CHANNEL_1, TIM_CCx_ENABLE);
3726 TIM_CCxChannelCmd(htim->Instance, TIM_CHANNEL_2, TIM_CCx_ENABLE);
3727
3728 /* Enable the Peripheral */
3729 __HAL_TIM_ENABLE(htim);
3730
3731 break;
3732 }
3733 }
3734
3735 /* Return function status */
3736 return HAL_OK;
3737}
3738
3749HAL_StatusTypeDef HAL_TIM_Encoder_Stop_DMA(TIM_HandleTypeDef *htim, uint32_t Channel)
3750{
3751 /* Check the parameters */
3752 assert_param(IS_TIM_ENCODER_INTERFACE_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
3753
3754 /* Disable the Input Capture channels 1 and 2
3755 (in the EncoderInterface the two possible channels that can be used are TIM_CHANNEL_1 and TIM_CHANNEL_2) */
3756 if (Channel == TIM_CHANNEL_1)
3757 {
3758 TIM_CCxChannelCmd(htim->Instance, TIM_CHANNEL_1, TIM_CCx_DISABLE);
3759
3760 /* Disable the capture compare DMA Request 1 */
3761 __HAL_TIM_DISABLE_DMA(htim, TIM_DMA_CC1);
3762 (void)HAL_DMA_Abort_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC1]);
3763 }
3764 else if (Channel == TIM_CHANNEL_2)
3765 {
3766 TIM_CCxChannelCmd(htim->Instance, TIM_CHANNEL_2, TIM_CCx_DISABLE);
3767
3768 /* Disable the capture compare DMA Request 2 */
3769 __HAL_TIM_DISABLE_DMA(htim, TIM_DMA_CC2);
3770 (void)HAL_DMA_Abort_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC2]);
3771 }
3772 else
3773 {
3774 TIM_CCxChannelCmd(htim->Instance, TIM_CHANNEL_1, TIM_CCx_DISABLE);
3775 TIM_CCxChannelCmd(htim->Instance, TIM_CHANNEL_2, TIM_CCx_DISABLE);
3776
3777 /* Disable the capture compare DMA Request 1 and 2 */
3778 __HAL_TIM_DISABLE_DMA(htim, TIM_DMA_CC1);
3779 __HAL_TIM_DISABLE_DMA(htim, TIM_DMA_CC2);
3780 (void)HAL_DMA_Abort_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC1]);
3781 (void)HAL_DMA_Abort_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC2]);
3782 }
3783
3784 /* Disable the Peripheral */
3785 __HAL_TIM_DISABLE(htim);
3786
3787 /* Set the TIM channel(s) state */
3788 if ((Channel == TIM_CHANNEL_1) || (Channel == TIM_CHANNEL_2))
3789 {
3790 TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_SET(htim, Channel, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY);
3791 TIM_CHANNEL_N_STATE_SET(htim, Channel, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY);
3792 }
3793 else
3794 {
3795 TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_1, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY);
3796 TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_2, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY);
3797 TIM_CHANNEL_N_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_1, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY);
3798 TIM_CHANNEL_N_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_2, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY);
3799 }
3800
3801 /* Return function status */
3802 return HAL_OK;
3803}
3804
3826void HAL_TIM_IRQHandler(TIM_HandleTypeDef *htim)
3827{
3828 /* Capture compare 1 event */
3829 if (__HAL_TIM_GET_FLAG(htim, TIM_FLAG_CC1) != RESET)
3830 {
3831 if (__HAL_TIM_GET_IT_SOURCE(htim, TIM_IT_CC1) != RESET)
3832 {
3833 {
3834 __HAL_TIM_CLEAR_IT(htim, TIM_IT_CC1);
3835 htim->Channel = HAL_TIM_ACTIVE_CHANNEL_1;
3836
3837 /* Input capture event */
3838 if ((htim->Instance->CCMR1 & TIM_CCMR1_CC1S) != 0x00U)
3839 {
3840#if (USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS == 1)
3841 htim->IC_CaptureCallback(htim);
3842#else
3843 HAL_TIM_IC_CaptureCallback(htim);
3844#endif /* USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS */
3845 }
3846 /* Output compare event */
3847 else
3848 {
3849#if (USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS == 1)
3850 htim->OC_DelayElapsedCallback(htim);
3851 htim->PWM_PulseFinishedCallback(htim);
3852#else
3853 HAL_TIM_OC_DelayElapsedCallback(htim);
3854 HAL_TIM_PWM_PulseFinishedCallback(htim);
3855#endif /* USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS */
3856 }
3857 htim->Channel = HAL_TIM_ACTIVE_CHANNEL_CLEARED;
3858 }
3859 }
3860 }
3861 /* Capture compare 2 event */
3862 if (__HAL_TIM_GET_FLAG(htim, TIM_FLAG_CC2) != RESET)
3863 {
3864 if (__HAL_TIM_GET_IT_SOURCE(htim, TIM_IT_CC2) != RESET)
3865 {
3866 __HAL_TIM_CLEAR_IT(htim, TIM_IT_CC2);
3867 htim->Channel = HAL_TIM_ACTIVE_CHANNEL_2;
3868 /* Input capture event */
3869 if ((htim->Instance->CCMR1 & TIM_CCMR1_CC2S) != 0x00U)
3870 {
3871#if (USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS == 1)
3872 htim->IC_CaptureCallback(htim);
3873#else
3874 HAL_TIM_IC_CaptureCallback(htim);
3875#endif /* USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS */
3876 }
3877 /* Output compare event */
3878 else
3879 {
3880#if (USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS == 1)
3881 htim->OC_DelayElapsedCallback(htim);
3882 htim->PWM_PulseFinishedCallback(htim);
3883#else
3884 HAL_TIM_OC_DelayElapsedCallback(htim);
3885 HAL_TIM_PWM_PulseFinishedCallback(htim);
3886#endif /* USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS */
3887 }
3888 htim->Channel = HAL_TIM_ACTIVE_CHANNEL_CLEARED;
3889 }
3890 }
3891 /* Capture compare 3 event */
3892 if (__HAL_TIM_GET_FLAG(htim, TIM_FLAG_CC3) != RESET)
3893 {
3894 if (__HAL_TIM_GET_IT_SOURCE(htim, TIM_IT_CC3) != RESET)
3895 {
3896 __HAL_TIM_CLEAR_IT(htim, TIM_IT_CC3);
3897 htim->Channel = HAL_TIM_ACTIVE_CHANNEL_3;
3898 /* Input capture event */
3899 if ((htim->Instance->CCMR2 & TIM_CCMR2_CC3S) != 0x00U)
3900 {
3901#if (USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS == 1)
3902 htim->IC_CaptureCallback(htim);
3903#else
3904 HAL_TIM_IC_CaptureCallback(htim);
3905#endif /* USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS */
3906 }
3907 /* Output compare event */
3908 else
3909 {
3910#if (USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS == 1)
3911 htim->OC_DelayElapsedCallback(htim);
3912 htim->PWM_PulseFinishedCallback(htim);
3913#else
3914 HAL_TIM_OC_DelayElapsedCallback(htim);
3915 HAL_TIM_PWM_PulseFinishedCallback(htim);
3916#endif /* USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS */
3917 }
3918 htim->Channel = HAL_TIM_ACTIVE_CHANNEL_CLEARED;
3919 }
3920 }
3921 /* Capture compare 4 event */
3922 if (__HAL_TIM_GET_FLAG(htim, TIM_FLAG_CC4) != RESET)
3923 {
3924 if (__HAL_TIM_GET_IT_SOURCE(htim, TIM_IT_CC4) != RESET)
3925 {
3926 __HAL_TIM_CLEAR_IT(htim, TIM_IT_CC4);
3927 htim->Channel = HAL_TIM_ACTIVE_CHANNEL_4;
3928 /* Input capture event */
3929 if ((htim->Instance->CCMR2 & TIM_CCMR2_CC4S) != 0x00U)
3930 {
3931#if (USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS == 1)
3932 htim->IC_CaptureCallback(htim);
3933#else
3934 HAL_TIM_IC_CaptureCallback(htim);
3935#endif /* USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS */
3936 }
3937 /* Output compare event */
3938 else
3939 {
3940#if (USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS == 1)
3941 htim->OC_DelayElapsedCallback(htim);
3942 htim->PWM_PulseFinishedCallback(htim);
3943#else
3944 HAL_TIM_OC_DelayElapsedCallback(htim);
3945 HAL_TIM_PWM_PulseFinishedCallback(htim);
3946#endif /* USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS */
3947 }
3948 htim->Channel = HAL_TIM_ACTIVE_CHANNEL_CLEARED;
3949 }
3950 }
3951 /* TIM Update event */
3952 if (__HAL_TIM_GET_FLAG(htim, TIM_FLAG_UPDATE) != RESET)
3953 {
3954 if (__HAL_TIM_GET_IT_SOURCE(htim, TIM_IT_UPDATE) != RESET)
3955 {
3956 __HAL_TIM_CLEAR_IT(htim, TIM_IT_UPDATE);
3957#if (USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS == 1)
3958 htim->PeriodElapsedCallback(htim);
3959#else
3960 HAL_TIM_PeriodElapsedCallback(htim);
3961#endif /* USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS */
3962 }
3963 }
3964 /* TIM Break input event */
3965 if (__HAL_TIM_GET_FLAG(htim, TIM_FLAG_BREAK) != RESET)
3966 {
3967 if (__HAL_TIM_GET_IT_SOURCE(htim, TIM_IT_BREAK) != RESET)
3968 {
3969 __HAL_TIM_CLEAR_IT(htim, TIM_IT_BREAK);
3970#if (USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS == 1)
3971 htim->BreakCallback(htim);
3972#else
3973 HAL_TIMEx_BreakCallback(htim);
3974#endif /* USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS */
3975 }
3976 }
3977 /* TIM Break2 input event */
3978 if (__HAL_TIM_GET_FLAG(htim, TIM_FLAG_BREAK2) != RESET)
3979 {
3980 if (__HAL_TIM_GET_IT_SOURCE(htim, TIM_IT_BREAK) != RESET)
3981 {
3982 __HAL_TIM_CLEAR_FLAG(htim, TIM_FLAG_BREAK2);
3983#if (USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS == 1)
3984 htim->Break2Callback(htim);
3985#else
3986 HAL_TIMEx_Break2Callback(htim);
3987#endif /* USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS */
3988 }
3989 }
3990 /* TIM Trigger detection event */
3991 if (__HAL_TIM_GET_FLAG(htim, TIM_FLAG_TRIGGER) != RESET)
3992 {
3993 if (__HAL_TIM_GET_IT_SOURCE(htim, TIM_IT_TRIGGER) != RESET)
3994 {
3995 __HAL_TIM_CLEAR_IT(htim, TIM_IT_TRIGGER);
3996#if (USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS == 1)
3997 htim->TriggerCallback(htim);
3998#else
3999 HAL_TIM_TriggerCallback(htim);
4000#endif /* USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS */
4001 }
4002 }
4003 /* TIM commutation event */
4004 if (__HAL_TIM_GET_FLAG(htim, TIM_FLAG_COM) != RESET)
4005 {
4006 if (__HAL_TIM_GET_IT_SOURCE(htim, TIM_IT_COM) != RESET)
4007 {
4008 __HAL_TIM_CLEAR_IT(htim, TIM_FLAG_COM);
4009#if (USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS == 1)
4010 htim->CommutationCallback(htim);
4011#else
4012 HAL_TIMEx_CommutCallback(htim);
4013#endif /* USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS */
4014 }
4015 }
4016}

4056HAL_StatusTypeDef HAL_TIM_OC_ConfigChannel(TIM_HandleTypeDef *htim,
4057 TIM_OC_InitTypeDef *sConfig,
4058 uint32_t Channel)
4059{
4060 HAL_StatusTypeDef status = HAL_OK;
4061
4062 /* Check the parameters */
4063 assert_param(IS_TIM_CHANNELS(Channel));
4064 assert_param(IS_TIM_OC_MODE(sConfig->OCMode));
4065 assert_param(IS_TIM_OC_POLARITY(sConfig->OCPolarity));
4066
4067 /* Process Locked */
4068 __HAL_LOCK(htim);
4069
4070 switch (Channel)
4071 {
4072 case TIM_CHANNEL_1:
4073 {
4074 /* Check the parameters */
4075 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC1_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
4076
4077 /* Configure the TIM Channel 1 in Output Compare */
4078 TIM_OC1_SetConfig(htim->Instance, sConfig);
4079 break;
4080 }
4081
4082 case TIM_CHANNEL_2:
4083 {
4084 /* Check the parameters */
4085 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC2_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
4086
4087 /* Configure the TIM Channel 2 in Output Compare */
4088 TIM_OC2_SetConfig(htim->Instance, sConfig);
4089 break;
4090 }
4091
4092 case TIM_CHANNEL_3:
4093 {
4094 /* Check the parameters */
4095 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC3_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
4096
4097 /* Configure the TIM Channel 3 in Output Compare */
4098 TIM_OC3_SetConfig(htim->Instance, sConfig);
4099 break;
4100 }
4101
4102 case TIM_CHANNEL_4:
4103 {
4104 /* Check the parameters */
4105 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC4_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
4106
4107 /* Configure the TIM Channel 4 in Output Compare */
4108 TIM_OC4_SetConfig(htim->Instance, sConfig);
4109 break;
4110 }
4111
4112 case TIM_CHANNEL_5:
4113 {
4114 /* Check the parameters */
4115 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC5_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
4116
4117 /* Configure the TIM Channel 5 in Output Compare */
4118 TIM_OC5_SetConfig(htim->Instance, sConfig);
4119 break;
4120 }
4121
4122 case TIM_CHANNEL_6:
4123 {
4124 /* Check the parameters */
4125 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC6_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
4126
4127 /* Configure the TIM Channel 6 in Output Compare */
4128 TIM_OC6_SetConfig(htim->Instance, sConfig);
4129 break;
4130 }
4131
4132 default:
4133 status = HAL_ERROR;
4134 break;
4135 }
4136
4137 __HAL_UNLOCK(htim);
4138
4139 return status;
4140}

4155HAL_StatusTypeDef HAL_TIM_IC_ConfigChannel(TIM_HandleTypeDef *htim, TIM_IC_InitTypeDef *sConfig, uint32_t Channel)
4156{
4157 HAL_StatusTypeDef status = HAL_OK;
4158
4159 /* Check the parameters */
4160 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC1_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
4161 assert_param(IS_TIM_IC_POLARITY(sConfig->ICPolarity));
4162 assert_param(IS_TIM_IC_SELECTION(sConfig->ICSelection));
4163 assert_param(IS_TIM_IC_PRESCALER(sConfig->ICPrescaler));
4164 assert_param(IS_TIM_IC_FILTER(sConfig->ICFilter));
4165
4166 /* Process Locked */
4167 __HAL_LOCK(htim);
4168
4169 if (Channel == TIM_CHANNEL_1)
4170 {
4171 /* TI1 Configuration */
4172 TIM_TI1_SetConfig(htim->Instance,
4173 sConfig->ICPolarity,
4174 sConfig->ICSelection,
4175 sConfig->ICFilter);
4176
4177 /* Reset the IC1PSC Bits */
4178 htim->Instance->CCMR1 &= ~TIM_CCMR1_IC1PSC;
4179
4180 /* Set the IC1PSC value */
4181 htim->Instance->CCMR1 |= sConfig->ICPrescaler;
4182 }
4183 else if (Channel == TIM_CHANNEL_2)
4184 {
4185 /* TI2 Configuration */
4186 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC2_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
4187
4188 TIM_TI2_SetConfig(htim->Instance,
4189 sConfig->ICPolarity,
4190 sConfig->ICSelection,
4191 sConfig->ICFilter);
4192
4193 /* Reset the IC2PSC Bits */
4194 htim->Instance->CCMR1 &= ~TIM_CCMR1_IC2PSC;
4195
4196 /* Set the IC2PSC value */
4197 htim->Instance->CCMR1 |= (sConfig->ICPrescaler << 8U);
4198 }
4199 else if (Channel == TIM_CHANNEL_3)
4200 {
4201 /* TI3 Configuration */
4202 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC3_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
4203
4204 TIM_TI3_SetConfig(htim->Instance,
4205 sConfig->ICPolarity,
4206 sConfig->ICSelection,
4207 sConfig->ICFilter);
4208
4209 /* Reset the IC3PSC Bits */
4210 htim->Instance->CCMR2 &= ~TIM_CCMR2_IC3PSC;
4211
4212 /* Set the IC3PSC value */
4213 htim->Instance->CCMR2 |= sConfig->ICPrescaler;
4214 }
4215 else if (Channel == TIM_CHANNEL_4)
4216 {
4217 /* TI4 Configuration */
4218 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC4_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
4219
4220 TIM_TI4_SetConfig(htim->Instance,
4221 sConfig->ICPolarity,
4222 sConfig->ICSelection,
4223 sConfig->ICFilter);
4224
4225 /* Reset the IC4PSC Bits */
4226 htim->Instance->CCMR2 &= ~TIM_CCMR2_IC4PSC;
4227
4228 /* Set the IC4PSC value */
4229 htim->Instance->CCMR2 |= (sConfig->ICPrescaler << 8U);
4230 }
4231 else
4232 {
4233 status = HAL_ERROR;
4234 }
4235
4236 __HAL_UNLOCK(htim);
4237
4238 return status;
4239}

4256HAL_StatusTypeDef HAL_TIM_PWM_ConfigChannel(TIM_HandleTypeDef *htim,
4257 TIM_OC_InitTypeDef *sConfig,
4258 uint32_t Channel)
4259{
4260 HAL_StatusTypeDef status = HAL_OK;
4261
4262 /* Check the parameters */
4263 assert_param(IS_TIM_CHANNELS(Channel));
4264 assert_param(IS_TIM_PWM_MODE(sConfig->OCMode));
4265 assert_param(IS_TIM_OC_POLARITY(sConfig->OCPolarity));
4266 assert_param(IS_TIM_FAST_STATE(sConfig->OCFastMode));
4267
4268 /* Process Locked */
4269 __HAL_LOCK(htim);
4270
4271 switch (Channel)
4272 {
4273 case TIM_CHANNEL_1:
4274 {
4275 /* Check the parameters */
4276 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC1_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
4277
4278 /* Configure the Channel 1 in PWM mode */
4279 TIM_OC1_SetConfig(htim->Instance, sConfig);
4280
4281 /* Set the Preload enable bit for channel1 */
4282 htim->Instance->CCMR1 |= TIM_CCMR1_OC1PE;
4283
4284 /* Configure the Output Fast mode */
4285 htim->Instance->CCMR1 &= ~TIM_CCMR1_OC1FE;
4286 htim->Instance->CCMR1 |= sConfig->OCFastMode;
4287 break;
4288 }
4289
4290 case TIM_CHANNEL_2:
4291 {
4292 /* Check the parameters */
4293 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC2_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
4294
4295 /* Configure the Channel 2 in PWM mode */
4296 TIM_OC2_SetConfig(htim->Instance, sConfig);
4297
4298 /* Set the Preload enable bit for channel2 */
4299 htim->Instance->CCMR1 |= TIM_CCMR1_OC2PE;
4300
4301 /* Configure the Output Fast mode */
4302 htim->Instance->CCMR1 &= ~TIM_CCMR1_OC2FE;
4303 htim->Instance->CCMR1 |= sConfig->OCFastMode << 8U;
4304 break;
4305 }
4306
4307 case TIM_CHANNEL_3:
4308 {
4309 /* Check the parameters */
4310 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC3_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
4311
4312 /* Configure the Channel 3 in PWM mode */

4314
4315 /* Set the Preload enable bit for channel3 */
4316 htim->Instance->CCMR2 |= TIM_CCMR2_OC3PE;
4317
4318 /* Configure the Output Fast mode */
4319 htim->Instance->CCMR2 &= ~TIM_CCMR2_OC3FE;
4320 htim->Instance->CCMR2 |= sConfig->OCFastMode;
4321 break;
4322 }
4323
4324 case TIM_CHANNEL_4:
4325 {
4326 /* Check the parameters */
4327 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC4_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
4328
4329 /* Configure the Channel 4 in PWM mode */
4330 TIM_OC4_SetConfig(htim->Instance, sConfig);
4331
4332 /* Set the Preload enable bit for channel4 */
4333 htim->Instance->CCMR2 |= TIM_CCMR2_OC4PE;
4334
4335 /* Configure the Output Fast mode */
4336 htim->Instance->CCMR2 &= ~TIM_CCMR2_OC4FE;
4337 htim->Instance->CCMR2 |= sConfig->OCFastMode << 8U;
4338 break;
4339 }
4340
4341 case TIM_CHANNEL_5:
4342 {
4343 /* Check the parameters */
4344 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC5_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
4345
4346 /* Configure the Channel 5 in PWM mode */
4347 TIM_OC5_SetConfig(htim->Instance, sConfig);
4348
4349 /* Set the Preload enable bit for channel5*/
4350 htim->Instance->CCMR3 |= TIM_CCMR3_OC5PE;
4351
4352 /* Configure the Output Fast mode */
4353 htim->Instance->CCMR3 &= ~TIM_CCMR3_OC5FE;
4354 htim->Instance->CCMR3 |= sConfig->OCFastMode;
4355 break;
4356 }
4357
4358 case TIM_CHANNEL_6:
4359 {
4360 /* Check the parameters */
4361 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC6_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
4362
4363 /* Configure the Channel 6 in PWM mode */
4364 TIM_OC6_SetConfig(htim->Instance, sConfig);
4365
4366 /* Set the Preload enable bit for channel6 */
4367 htim->Instance->CCMR3 |= TIM_CCMR3_OC6PE;
4368
4369 /* Configure the Output Fast mode */
4370 htim->Instance->CCMR3 &= ~TIM_CCMR3_OC6FE;
4371 htim->Instance->CCMR3 |= sConfig->OCFastMode << 8U;

4384
4404HAL_StatusTypeDef HAL_TIM_OnePulse_ConfigChannel(TIM_HandleTypeDef *htim, TIM_OnePulse_InitTypeDef *sConfig,
4405 uint32_t OutputChannel, uint32_t InputChannel)
4406{
4407 HAL_StatusTypeDef status = HAL_OK;
4408 TIM_OC_InitTypeDef temp1;
4409
4410 /* Check the parameters */
4411 assert_param(IS_TIM_OPM_CHANNELS(OutputChannel));
4412 assert_param(IS_TIM_OPM_CHANNELS(InputChannel));
4413
4414 if (OutputChannel != InputChannel)
4415 {
4416 /* Process Locked */
4417 __HAL_LOCK(htim);
4418
4419 htim->State = HAL_TIM_STATE_BUSY;
4420
4421 /* Extract the Output compare configuration from sConfig structure */
4422 temp1.OCMode = sConfig->OCMode;
4423 temp1.Pulse = sConfig->Pulse;
4424 temp1.OCPolarity = sConfig->OCPolarity;
4425 temp1.OCNPolarity = sConfig->OCNPolarity;
4426 temp1.OCIdleState = sConfig->OCIdleState;
4427 temp1.OCNIdleState = sConfig->OCNIdleState;
4428
4429 switch (OutputChannel)
4430 {
4431 case TIM_CHANNEL_1:
4432 {
4433 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC1_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
4434
4435 TIM_OC1_SetConfig(htim->Instance, &temp1);
4436 break;
4437 }
4438
4439 case TIM_CHANNEL_2:
4440 {
4441 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC2_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
4442
4443 TIM_OC2_SetConfig(htim->Instance, &temp1);
4444 break;
4445 }
4446
4447 default:
4448 status = HAL_ERROR;
4449 break;
4450 }
4451
4452 if (status == HAL_OK)
4453 {
4454 switch (InputChannel)
4455 {
4456 case TIM_CHANNEL_1:
4457 {
4458 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC1_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
4459
4460 TIM_TI1_SetConfig(htim->Instance, sConfig->ICPolarity,
4461 sConfig->ICSelection, sConfig->ICFilter);
4462
4463 /* Reset the IC1PSC Bits */
4464 htim->Instance->CCMR1 &= ~TIM_CCMR1_IC1PSC;
4465
4466 /* Select the Trigger source */
4467 htim->Instance->SMCR &= ~TIM_SMCR_TS;
4468 htim->Instance->SMCR |= TIM_TS_TI1FP1;
4469
4470 /* Select the Slave Mode */
4471 htim->Instance->SMCR &= ~TIM_SMCR_SMS;
4472 htim->Instance->SMCR |= TIM_SLAVEMODE_TRIGGER;
4473 break;
4474 }
4475
4476 case TIM_CHANNEL_2:
4477 {
4478 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC2_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
4479
4480 TIM_TI2_SetConfig(htim->Instance, sConfig->ICPolarity,
4481 sConfig->ICSelection, sConfig->ICFilter);
4482
4483 /* Reset the IC2PSC Bits */
4484 htim->Instance->CCMR1 &= ~TIM_CCMR1_IC2PSC;
4485
4486 /* Select the Trigger source */
4487 htim->Instance->SMCR &= ~TIM_SMCR_TS;
4488 htim->Instance->SMCR |= TIM_TS_TI2FP2;
4489
4490 /* Select the Slave Mode */
4491 htim->Instance->SMCR &= ~TIM_SMCR_SMS;
4492 htim->Instance->SMCR |= TIM_SLAVEMODE_TRIGGER;
4493 break;
4494 }
4495
4496 default:
4497 status = HAL_ERROR;
4498 break;
4499 }
4500 }
4501
4502 htim->State = HAL_TIM_STATE_READY;
4503
4504 __HAL_UNLOCK(htim);
4505
4506 return status;
4507 }
4508 else
4509 {
4510 return HAL_ERROR;
4511 }
4512}

4558HAL_StatusTypeDef HAL_TIM_DMABurst_WriteStart(TIM_HandleTypeDef *htim, uint32_t BurstBaseAddress,
4559 uint32_t BurstRequestSrc, uint32_t *BurstBuffer, uint32_t BurstLength)
4560{
4561 HAL_StatusTypeDef status;
4562
4563 status = HAL_TIM_DMABurst_MultiWriteStart(htim, BurstBaseAddress, BurstRequestSrc, BurstBuffer, BurstLength,
4564 ((BurstLength) >> 8U) + 1U);
4565
4566
4567
4568 return status;
4569}
4570
4616HAL_StatusTypeDef HAL_TIM_DMABurst_MultiWriteStart(TIM_HandleTypeDef *htim, uint32_t BurstBaseAddress,
4617 uint32_t BurstRequestSrc, uint32_t *BurstBuffer,
4618 uint32_t BurstLength, uint32_t DataLength)
4619{
4620 HAL_StatusTypeDef status = HAL_OK;
4621
4622 /* Check the parameters */
4623 assert_param(IS_TIM_DMABURST_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
4624 assert_param(IS_TIM_DMA_BASE(BurstBaseAddress));
4625 assert_param(IS_TIM_DMA_SOURCE(BurstRequestSrc));
4626 assert_param(IS_TIM_DMA_LENGTH(BurstLength));
4627 assert_param(IS_TIM_DMA_DATA_LENGTH(DataLength));
4628
4629 if (htim->DMABurstState == HAL_DMA_BURST_STATE_BUSY)
4630 {
4631 return HAL_BUSY;
4632 }
4633 else if (htim->DMABurstState == HAL_DMA_BURST_STATE_READY)
4634 {
4635 if ((BurstBuffer == NULL) && (BurstLength > 0U))
4636 {
4637 return HAL_ERROR;
4638 }
4639 else
4640 {
4641 htim->DMABurstState = HAL_DMA_BURST_STATE_BUSY;
4642 }
4643 }
4644 else
4645 {
4646 /* nothing to do */
4647 }
4648
4649 switch (BurstRequestSrc)
4650 {
4651 case TIM_DMA_UPDATE:
4652 {
4653 /* Set the DMA Period elapsed callbacks */
4654 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_UPDATE]->XferCpltCallback = TIM_DMAPeriodElapsedCplt;
4655 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_UPDATE]->XferHalfCpltCallback = TIM_DMAPeriodElapsedHalfCplt;
4656
4657 /* Set the DMA error callback */
4658 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_UPDATE]->XferErrorCallback = TIM_DMAError ;
4659
4660 /* Enable the DMA channel */
4661 if (HAL_DMA_Start_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_UPDATE], (uint32_t)BurstBuffer,
4662 (uint32_t)&htim->Instance->DMAR, DataLength) != HAL_OK)
4663 {
4664 /* Return error status */
4665 return HAL_ERROR;
4666 }
4667 break;
4668 }
4669 case TIM_DMA_CC1:
4670 {
4671 /* Set the DMA compare callbacks */
4672 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC1]->XferCpltCallback = TIM_DMADelayPulseCplt;
4673 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC1]->XferHalfCpltCallback = TIM_DMADelayPulseHalfCplt;
4674
4675 /* Set the DMA error callback */
4676 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC1]->XferErrorCallback = TIM_DMAError ;
4677
4678 /* Enable the DMA channel */
4679 if (HAL_DMA_Start_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC1], (uint32_t)BurstBuffer,
4680 (uint32_t)&htim->Instance->DMAR, DataLength) != HAL_OK)
4681 {
4682 /* Return error status */
4683 return HAL_ERROR;
4684 }
4685 break;
4686 }
4687 case TIM_DMA_CC2:
4688 {
4689 /* Set the DMA compare callbacks */
4690 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC2]->XferCpltCallback = TIM_DMADelayPulseCplt;
4691 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC2]->XferHalfCpltCallback = TIM_DMADelayPulseHalfCplt;
4692
4693 /* Set the DMA error callback */
4694 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC2]->XferErrorCallback = TIM_DMAError ;
4695
4696 /* Enable the DMA channel */
4697 if (HAL_DMA_Start_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC2], (uint32_t)BurstBuffer,
4698 (uint32_t)&htim->Instance->DMAR, DataLength) != HAL_OK)
4699 {
4700 /* Return error status */
4701 return HAL_ERROR;
4702 }
4703 break;
4704 }
4705 case TIM_DMA_CC3:
4706 {
4707 /* Set the DMA compare callbacks */
4708 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC3]->XferCpltCallback = TIM_DMADelayPulseCplt;
4709 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC3]->XferHalfCpltCallback = TIM_DMADelayPulseHalfCplt;
4710
4711 /* Set the DMA error callback */
4712 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC3]->XferErrorCallback = TIM_DMAError ;
4713
4714 /* Enable the DMA channel */
4715 if (HAL_DMA_Start_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC3], (uint32_t)BurstBuffer,
4716 (uint32_t)&htim->Instance->DMAR, DataLength) != HAL_OK)
4717 {
4718 /* Return error status */
4719 return HAL_ERROR;
4720 }
4721 break;
4722 }
4723 case TIM_DMA_CC4:
4724 {
4725 /* Set the DMA compare callbacks */
4726 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC4]->XferCpltCallback = TIM_DMADelayPulseCplt;
4727 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC4]->XferHalfCpltCallback = TIM_DMADelayPulseHalfCplt;
4728
4729 /* Set the DMA error callback */
4730 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC4]->XferErrorCallback = TIM_DMAError ;
4731
4732 /* Enable the DMA channel */
4733 if (HAL_DMA_Start_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC4], (uint32_t)BurstBuffer,
4734 (uint32_t)&htim->Instance->DMAR, DataLength) != HAL_OK)
4735 {
4736 /* Return error status */
4737 return HAL_ERROR;
4738 }
4739 break;
4740 }
4741 case TIM_DMA_COM:
4742 {
4743 /* Set the DMA commutation callbacks */
4744 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_COMMUTATION]->XferCpltCallback = TIMEx_DMACommutationCplt;
4745 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_COMMUTATION]->XferHalfCpltCallback = TIMEx_DMACommutationHalfCplt;
4746
4747 /* Set the DMA error callback */
4748 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_COMMUTATION]->XferErrorCallback = TIM_DMAError ;
4749
4750 /* Enable the DMA channel */
4751 if (HAL_DMA_Start_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_COMMUTATION], (uint32_t)BurstBuffer,
4752 (uint32_t)&htim->Instance->DMAR, DataLength) != HAL_OK)
4753 {
4754 /* Return error status */
4755 return HAL_ERROR;
4756 }
4757 break;
4758 }
4759 case TIM_DMA_TRIGGER:
4760 {
4761 /* Set the DMA trigger callbacks */
4762 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_TRIGGER]->XferCpltCallback = TIM_DMATriggerCplt;
4763 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_TRIGGER]->XferHalfCpltCallback = TIM_DMATriggerHalfCplt;
4764
4765 /* Set the DMA error callback */
4766 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_TRIGGER]->XferErrorCallback = TIM_DMAError ;
4767
4768 /* Enable the DMA channel */
4769 if (HAL_DMA_Start_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_TRIGGER], (uint32_t)BurstBuffer,
4770 (uint32_t)&htim->Instance->DMAR, DataLength) != HAL_OK)
4771 {
4772 /* Return error status */
4773 return HAL_ERROR;
4774 }
4775 break;
4776 }
4777 default:
4778 status = HAL_ERROR;
4779 break;
4780 }
4781
4782 if (status == HAL_OK)
4783 {
4784 /* Configure the DMA Burst Mode */
4785 htim->Instance->DCR = (BurstBaseAddress | BurstLength);
4786 /* Enable the TIM DMA Request */
4787 __HAL_TIM_ENABLE_DMA(htim, BurstRequestSrc);
4788 }
4789
4790 /* Return function status */
4791 return status;
4792}
4793
4800HAL_StatusTypeDef HAL_TIM_DMABurst_WriteStop(TIM_HandleTypeDef *htim, uint32_t BurstRequestSrc)
4801{
4802 HAL_StatusTypeDef status = HAL_OK;
4803
4804 /* Check the parameters */
4805 assert_param(IS_TIM_DMA_SOURCE(BurstRequestSrc));
4806
4807 /* Abort the DMA transfer (at least disable the DMA channel) */
4808 switch (BurstRequestSrc)
4809 {
4810 case TIM_DMA_UPDATE:
4811 {
4812 (void)HAL_DMA_Abort_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_UPDATE]);
4813 break;
4814 }
4815 case TIM_DMA_CC1:
4816 {
4817 (void)HAL_DMA_Abort_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC1]);
4818 break;
4819 }
4820 case TIM_DMA_CC2:
4821 {
4822 (void)HAL_DMA_Abort_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC2]);
4823 break;
4824 }
4825 case TIM_DMA_CC3:
4826 {
4827 (void)HAL_DMA_Abort_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC3]);
4828 break;
4829 }
4830 case TIM_DMA_CC4:
4831 {
4832 (void)HAL_DMA_Abort_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC4]);
4833 break;
4834 }
4835 case TIM_DMA_COM:
4836 {
4837 (void)HAL_DMA_Abort_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_COMMUTATION]);
4838 break;
4839 }
4840 case TIM_DMA_TRIGGER:
4841 {
4842 (void)HAL_DMA_Abort_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_TRIGGER]);
4843 break;
4844 }
4845 default:
4846 status = HAL_ERROR;
4847 break;
4848 }
4849
4850 if (status == HAL_OK)
4851 {
4852 /* Disable the TIM Update DMA request */
4853 __HAL_TIM_DISABLE_DMA(htim, BurstRequestSrc);
4854
4855 /* Change the DMA burst operation state */
4856 htim->DMABurstState = HAL_DMA_BURST_STATE_READY;
4857 }
4858
4859 /* Return function status */
4860 return status;
4861}

4908 uint32_t BurstRequestSrc, uint32_t *BurstBuffer, uint32_t BurstLength)
4909{
4910 HAL_StatusTypeDef status;
4911
4912 status = HAL_TIM_DMABurst_MultiReadStart(htim, BurstBaseAddress, BurstRequestSrc, BurstBuffer, BurstLength,
4913 ((BurstLength) >> 8U) + 1U);

4916 return status;

4918
4964HAL_StatusTypeDef HAL_TIM_DMABurst_MultiReadStart(TIM_HandleTypeDef *htim, uint32_t BurstBaseAddress,
4965 uint32_t BurstRequestSrc, uint32_t *BurstBuffer,
4966 uint32_t BurstLength, uint32_t DataLength)
4967{
4968 HAL_StatusTypeDef status = HAL_OK;
4969
4970 /* Check the parameters */
4971 assert_param(IS_TIM_DMABURST_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
4972 assert_param(IS_TIM_DMA_BASE(BurstBaseAddress));
4973 assert_param(IS_TIM_DMA_SOURCE(BurstRequestSrc));
4974 assert_param(IS_TIM_DMA_LENGTH(BurstLength));
4975 assert_param(IS_TIM_DMA_DATA_LENGTH(DataLength));
4976
4977 if (htim->DMABurstState == HAL_DMA_BURST_STATE_BUSY)
4978 {
4979 return HAL_BUSY;
4980 }
4981 else if (htim->DMABurstState == HAL_DMA_BURST_STATE_READY)
4982 {
4983 if ((BurstBuffer == NULL) && (BurstLength > 0U))
4984 {
4985 return HAL_ERROR;
4986 }
4987 else
4988 {
4989 htim->DMABurstState = HAL_DMA_BURST_STATE_BUSY;
4990 }
4991 }
4992 else
4993 {
4994 /* nothing to do */
4995 }
4996 switch (BurstRequestSrc)
4997 {
4998 case TIM_DMA_UPDATE:
4999 {
5000 /* Set the DMA Period elapsed callbacks */
5001 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_UPDATE]->XferCpltCallback = TIM_DMAPeriodElapsedCplt;
5002 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_UPDATE]->XferHalfCpltCallback = TIM_DMAPeriodElapsedHalfCplt;
5003
5004 /* Set the DMA error callback */
5005 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_UPDATE]->XferErrorCallback = TIM_DMAError ;
5006
5007 /* Enable the DMA channel */
5008 if (HAL_DMA_Start_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_UPDATE], (uint32_t)&htim->Instance->DMAR, (uint32_t)BurstBuffer,
5009 DataLength) != HAL_OK)
5010 {
5011 /* Return error status */
5012 return HAL_ERROR;
5013 }
5014 break;
5015 }
5016 case TIM_DMA_CC1:
5017 {
5018 /* Set the DMA capture callbacks */
5019 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC1]->XferCpltCallback = TIM_DMACaptureCplt;
5020 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC1]->XferHalfCpltCallback = TIM_DMACaptureHalfCplt;
5021
5022 /* Set the DMA error callback */
5023 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC1]->XferErrorCallback = TIM_DMAError ;
5024
5025 /* Enable the DMA channel */
5026 if (HAL_DMA_Start_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC1], (uint32_t)&htim->Instance->DMAR, (uint32_t)BurstBuffer,
5027 DataLength) != HAL_OK)
5028 {
5029 /* Return error status */
5030 return HAL_ERROR;
5031 }
5032 break;
5033 }
5034 case TIM_DMA_CC2:
5035 {
5036 /* Set the DMA capture callbacks */
5037 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC2]->XferCpltCallback = TIM_DMACaptureCplt;
5038 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC2]->XferHalfCpltCallback = TIM_DMACaptureHalfCplt;
5039
5040 /* Set the DMA error callback */
5041 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC2]->XferErrorCallback = TIM_DMAError ;
5042
5043 /* Enable the DMA channel */
5044 if (HAL_DMA_Start_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC2], (uint32_t)&htim->Instance->DMAR, (uint32_t)BurstBuffer,
5045 DataLength) != HAL_OK)
5046 {
5047 /* Return error status */
5048 return HAL_ERROR;
5049 }
5050 break;
5051 }
5052 case TIM_DMA_CC3:
5053 {
5054 /* Set the DMA capture callbacks */
5055 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC3]->XferCpltCallback = TIM_DMACaptureCplt;
5056 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC3]->XferHalfCpltCallback = TIM_DMACaptureHalfCplt;
5057
5058 /* Set the DMA error callback */
5059 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC3]->XferErrorCallback = TIM_DMAError ;
5060
5061 /* Enable the DMA channel */
5062 if (HAL_DMA_Start_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC3], (uint32_t)&htim->Instance->DMAR, (uint32_t)BurstBuffer,
5063 DataLength) != HAL_OK)
5064 {
5065 /* Return error status */
5066 return HAL_ERROR;
5067 }
5068 break;
5069 }
5070 case TIM_DMA_CC4:
5071 {
5072 /* Set the DMA capture callbacks */
5073 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC4]->XferCpltCallback = TIM_DMACaptureCplt;
5074 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC4]->XferHalfCpltCallback = TIM_DMACaptureHalfCplt;
5075
5076 /* Set the DMA error callback */
5077 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC4]->XferErrorCallback = TIM_DMAError ;
5078
5079 /* Enable the DMA channel */
5080 if (HAL_DMA_Start_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC4], (uint32_t)&htim->Instance->DMAR, (uint32_t)BurstBuffer,
5081 DataLength) != HAL_OK)
5082 {
5083 /* Return error status */
5084 return HAL_ERROR;
5085 }
5086 break;
5087 }
5088 case TIM_DMA_COM:
5089 {
5090 /* Set the DMA commutation callbacks */
5091 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_COMMUTATION]->XferCpltCallback = TIMEx_DMACommutationCplt;
5092 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_COMMUTATION]->XferHalfCpltCallback = TIMEx_DMACommutationHalfCplt;
5093
5094 /* Set the DMA error callback */
5095 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_COMMUTATION]->XferErrorCallback = TIM_DMAError ;
5096
5097 /* Enable the DMA channel */
5098 if (HAL_DMA_Start_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_COMMUTATION], (uint32_t)&htim->Instance->DMAR, (uint32_t)BurstBuffer,
5099 DataLength) != HAL_OK)
5100 {
5101 /* Return error status */
5102 return HAL_ERROR;
5103 }
5104 break;
5105 }
5106 case TIM_DMA_TRIGGER:
5107 {
5108 /* Set the DMA trigger callbacks */
5109 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_TRIGGER]->XferCpltCallback = TIM_DMATriggerCplt;
5110 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_TRIGGER]->XferHalfCpltCallback = TIM_DMATriggerHalfCplt;
5111
5112 /* Set the DMA error callback */
5113 htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_TRIGGER]->XferErrorCallback = TIM_DMAError ;
5114
5115 /* Enable the DMA channel */
5116 if (HAL_DMA_Start_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_TRIGGER], (uint32_t)&htim->Instance->DMAR, (uint32_t)BurstBuffer,
5117 DataLength) != HAL_OK)
5118 {
5119 /* Return error status */
5120 return HAL_ERROR;
5121 }
5122 break;
5123 }
5124 default:
5125 status = HAL_ERROR;
5126 break;
5127 }
5128
5129 if (status == HAL_OK)
5130 {
5131 /* Configure the DMA Burst Mode */
5132 htim->Instance->DCR = (BurstBaseAddress | BurstLength);
5133
5134 /* Enable the TIM DMA Request */
5135 __HAL_TIM_ENABLE_DMA(htim, BurstRequestSrc);
5136 }
5137
5138 /* Return function status */
5139 return status;
5140}
5141
5148HAL_StatusTypeDef HAL_TIM_DMABurst_ReadStop(TIM_HandleTypeDef *htim, uint32_t BurstRequestSrc)
5149{
5150 HAL_StatusTypeDef status = HAL_OK;
5151
5152 /* Check the parameters */
5153 assert_param(IS_TIM_DMA_SOURCE(BurstRequestSrc));
5154
5155 /* Abort the DMA transfer (at least disable the DMA channel) */
5156 switch (BurstRequestSrc)
5157 {
5158 case TIM_DMA_UPDATE:
5159 {
5160 (void)HAL_DMA_Abort_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_UPDATE]);
5161 break;
5162 }
5163 case TIM_DMA_CC1:
5164 {
5165 (void)HAL_DMA_Abort_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC1]);
5166 break;
5167 }
5168 case TIM_DMA_CC2:
5169 {
5170 (void)HAL_DMA_Abort_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC2]);
5171 break;
5172 }
5173 case TIM_DMA_CC3:
5174 {
5175 (void)HAL_DMA_Abort_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC3]);
5176 break;
5177 }
5178 case TIM_DMA_CC4:
5179 {
5180 (void)HAL_DMA_Abort_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC4]);
5181 break;
5182 }
5183 case TIM_DMA_COM:
5184 {
5185 (void)HAL_DMA_Abort_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_COMMUTATION]);
5186 break;
5187 }
5188 case TIM_DMA_TRIGGER:
5189 {
5190 (void)HAL_DMA_Abort_IT(htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_TRIGGER]);
5191 break;
5192 }
5193 default:
5194 status = HAL_ERROR;
5195 break;
5196 }
5197
5198 if (status == HAL_OK)
5199 {
5200 /* Disable the TIM Update DMA request */
5201 __HAL_TIM_DISABLE_DMA(htim, BurstRequestSrc);
5202
5203 /* Change the DMA burst operation state */
5204 htim->DMABurstState = HAL_DMA_BURST_STATE_READY;
5205 }
5206
5207 /* Return function status */
5208 return status;
5209}

5255
5271HAL_StatusTypeDef HAL_TIM_ConfigOCrefClear(TIM_HandleTypeDef *htim,
5272 TIM_ClearInputConfigTypeDef *sClearInputConfig,
5273 uint32_t Channel)
5274{
5275 HAL_StatusTypeDef status = HAL_OK;
5276
5277 /* Check the parameters */
5278 assert_param(IS_TIM_OCXREF_CLEAR_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
5279 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLEARINPUT_SOURCE(sClearInputConfig->ClearInputSource));
5280
5281 /* Process Locked */
5282 __HAL_LOCK(htim);
5283
5284 htim->State = HAL_TIM_STATE_BUSY;
5285
5286 switch (sClearInputConfig->ClearInputSource)
5287 {
5288 case TIM_CLEARINPUTSOURCE_NONE:
5289 {
5290 /* Clear the OCREF clear selection bit and the the ETR Bits */
5291 CLEAR_BIT(htim->Instance->SMCR, (TIM_SMCR_OCCS | TIM_SMCR_ETF | TIM_SMCR_ETPS | TIM_SMCR_ECE | TIM_SMCR_ETP));
5292
5293 /* Clear TIMx_AF1_OCREF_CLR (reset value) */
5294 CLEAR_BIT(htim->Instance->AF1, TIM1_AF1_ETRSEL);
5295 break;
5296 }
5297 case TIM_CLEARINPUTSOURCE_COMP1:
5298 case TIM_CLEARINPUTSOURCE_COMP2:
5299 {
5300 /* Clear the OCREF clear selection bit */
5301 CLEAR_BIT(htim->Instance->SMCR, TIM_SMCR_OCCS);
5302
5303 /* OCREF_CLR_INT is connected to COMPx output */
5304 MODIFY_REG(htim->Instance->AF1, TIM1_AF1_ETRSEL, sClearInputConfig->ClearInputSource);
5305 break;
5306 }
5307
5308 case TIM_CLEARINPUTSOURCE_ETR:
5309 {
5310 /* Check the parameters */
5311 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLEARINPUT_POLARITY(sClearInputConfig->ClearInputPolarity));
5312 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLEARINPUT_PRESCALER(sClearInputConfig->ClearInputPrescaler));
5313 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLEARINPUT_FILTER(sClearInputConfig->ClearInputFilter));
5314
5315 /* When OCRef clear feature is used with ETR source, ETR prescaler must be off */
5316 if (sClearInputConfig->ClearInputPrescaler != TIM_CLEARINPUTPRESCALER_DIV1)
5317 {
5318 htim->State = HAL_TIM_STATE_READY;
5319 __HAL_UNLOCK(htim);
5320 return HAL_ERROR;
5321 }
5322
5323 TIM_ETR_SetConfig(htim->Instance,
5324 sClearInputConfig->ClearInputPrescaler,
5325 sClearInputConfig->ClearInputPolarity,
5326 sClearInputConfig->ClearInputFilter);
5327
5328 /* Set the OCREF clear selection bit */
5329 SET_BIT(htim->Instance->SMCR, TIM_SMCR_OCCS);
5330
5331 /* Clear TIMx_AF1_OCREF_CLR (reset value) */
5332 CLEAR_BIT(htim->Instance->AF1, TIM1_AF1_ETRSEL);
5333 break;
5334 }
5335
5336 default:
5337 status = HAL_ERROR;
5338 break;
5339 }
5340
5341 if (status == HAL_OK)
5342 {
5343 switch (Channel)
5344 {
5345 case TIM_CHANNEL_1:
5346 {
5347 if (sClearInputConfig->ClearInputState != (uint32_t)DISABLE)
5348 {
5349 /* Enable the OCREF clear feature for Channel 1 */
5350 SET_BIT(htim->Instance->CCMR1, TIM_CCMR1_OC1CE);
5351 }
5352 else
5353 {
5354 /* Disable the OCREF clear feature for Channel 1 */
5355 CLEAR_BIT(htim->Instance->CCMR1, TIM_CCMR1_OC1CE);
5356 }
5357 break;
5358 }
5359 case TIM_CHANNEL_2:
5360 {
5361 if (sClearInputConfig->ClearInputState != (uint32_t)DISABLE)
5362 {
5363 /* Enable the OCREF clear feature for Channel 2 */
5364 SET_BIT(htim->Instance->CCMR1, TIM_CCMR1_OC2CE);
5365 }
5366 else
5367 {
5368 /* Disable the OCREF clear feature for Channel 2 */
5369 CLEAR_BIT(htim->Instance->CCMR1, TIM_CCMR1_OC2CE);
5370 }
5371 break;
5372 }
5373 case TIM_CHANNEL_3:
5374 {
5375 if (sClearInputConfig->ClearInputState != (uint32_t)DISABLE)
5376 {
5377 /* Enable the OCREF clear feature for Channel 3 */
5378 SET_BIT(htim->Instance->CCMR2, TIM_CCMR2_OC3CE);
5379 }
5380 else
5381 {
5382 /* Disable the OCREF clear feature for Channel 3 */
5383 CLEAR_BIT(htim->Instance->CCMR2, TIM_CCMR2_OC3CE);
5384 }
5385 break;
5386 }
5387 case TIM_CHANNEL_4:
5388 {
5389 if (sClearInputConfig->ClearInputState != (uint32_t)DISABLE)
5390 {
5391 /* Enable the OCREF clear feature for Channel 4 */
5392 SET_BIT(htim->Instance->CCMR2, TIM_CCMR2_OC4CE);
5393 }
5394 else
5395 {
5396 /* Disable the OCREF clear feature for Channel 4 */
5397 CLEAR_BIT(htim->Instance->CCMR2, TIM_CCMR2_OC4CE);
5398 }
5399 break;
5400 }
5401 case TIM_CHANNEL_5:
5402 {
5403 if (sClearInputConfig->ClearInputState != (uint32_t)DISABLE)
5404 {
5405 /* Enable the OCREF clear feature for Channel 5 */
5406 SET_BIT(htim->Instance->CCMR3, TIM_CCMR3_OC5CE);
5407 }
5408 else
5409 {
5410 /* Disable the OCREF clear feature for Channel 5 */
5411 CLEAR_BIT(htim->Instance->CCMR3, TIM_CCMR3_OC5CE);
5412 }
5413 break;
5414 }
5415 case TIM_CHANNEL_6:
5416 {
5417 if (sClearInputConfig->ClearInputState != (uint32_t)DISABLE)
5418 {
5419 /* Enable the OCREF clear feature for Channel 6 */
5420 SET_BIT(htim->Instance->CCMR3, TIM_CCMR3_OC6CE);
5421 }
5422 else
5423 {
5424 /* Disable the OCREF clear feature for Channel 6 */
5425 CLEAR_BIT(htim->Instance->CCMR3, TIM_CCMR3_OC6CE);
5426 }
5427 break;
5428 }
5429 default:
5430 break;
5431 }
5432 }
5433
5434 htim->State = HAL_TIM_STATE_READY;
5435
5436 __HAL_UNLOCK(htim);
5437
5438 return status;
5439}
5440
5448HAL_StatusTypeDef HAL_TIM_ConfigClockSource(TIM_HandleTypeDef *htim, TIM_ClockConfigTypeDef *sClockSourceConfig)
5449{
5450 HAL_StatusTypeDef status = HAL_OK;
5451 uint32_t tmpsmcr;
5452
5453 /* Process Locked */
5454 __HAL_LOCK(htim);
5455
5456 htim->State = HAL_TIM_STATE_BUSY;
5457
5458 /* Check the parameters */
5459 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLOCKSOURCE(sClockSourceConfig->ClockSource));
5460
5461 /* Reset the SMS, TS, ECE, ETPS and ETRF bits */
5462 tmpsmcr = htim->Instance->SMCR;
5463 tmpsmcr &= ~(TIM_SMCR_SMS | TIM_SMCR_TS);
5464 tmpsmcr &= ~(TIM_SMCR_ETF | TIM_SMCR_ETPS | TIM_SMCR_ECE | TIM_SMCR_ETP);
5465 htim->Instance->SMCR = tmpsmcr;
5466
5467 switch (sClockSourceConfig->ClockSource)
5468 {
5469 case TIM_CLOCKSOURCE_INTERNAL:
5470 {
5471 assert_param(IS_TIM_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
5472 break;
5473 }
5474
5475 case TIM_CLOCKSOURCE_ETRMODE1:
5476 {
5477 /* Check whether or not the timer instance supports external trigger input mode 1 (ETRF)*/
5478 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLOCKSOURCE_ETRMODE1_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
5479
5480 /* Check ETR input conditioning related parameters */
5481 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLOCKPRESCALER(sClockSourceConfig->ClockPrescaler));
5482 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLOCKPOLARITY(sClockSourceConfig->ClockPolarity));
5483 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLOCKFILTER(sClockSourceConfig->ClockFilter));
5484
5485 /* Configure the ETR Clock source */
5486 TIM_ETR_SetConfig(htim->Instance,
5487 sClockSourceConfig->ClockPrescaler,
5488 sClockSourceConfig->ClockPolarity,
5489 sClockSourceConfig->ClockFilter);
5490
5491 /* Select the External clock mode1 and the ETRF trigger */
5492 tmpsmcr = htim->Instance->SMCR;
5493 tmpsmcr |= (TIM_SLAVEMODE_EXTERNAL1 | TIM_CLOCKSOURCE_ETRMODE1);
5494 /* Write to TIMx SMCR */
5495 htim->Instance->SMCR = tmpsmcr;
5496 break;
5497 }
5498
5499 case TIM_CLOCKSOURCE_ETRMODE2:
5500 {
5501 /* Check whether or not the timer instance supports external trigger input mode 2 (ETRF)*/
5502 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLOCKSOURCE_ETRMODE2_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
5503
5504 /* Check ETR input conditioning related parameters */
5505 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLOCKPRESCALER(sClockSourceConfig->ClockPrescaler));
5506 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLOCKPOLARITY(sClockSourceConfig->ClockPolarity));
5507 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLOCKFILTER(sClockSourceConfig->ClockFilter));
5508
5509 /* Configure the ETR Clock source */
5510 TIM_ETR_SetConfig(htim->Instance,
5511 sClockSourceConfig->ClockPrescaler,
5512 sClockSourceConfig->ClockPolarity,
5513 sClockSourceConfig->ClockFilter);
5514 /* Enable the External clock mode2 */
5515 htim->Instance->SMCR |= TIM_SMCR_ECE;
5516 break;
5517 }
5518
5519 case TIM_CLOCKSOURCE_TI1:
5520 {
5521 /* Check whether or not the timer instance supports external clock mode 1 */
5522 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLOCKSOURCE_TIX_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
5523
5524 /* Check TI1 input conditioning related parameters */
5525 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLOCKPOLARITY(sClockSourceConfig->ClockPolarity));
5526 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLOCKFILTER(sClockSourceConfig->ClockFilter));
5527
5528 TIM_TI1_ConfigInputStage(htim->Instance,
5529 sClockSourceConfig->ClockPolarity,
5530 sClockSourceConfig->ClockFilter);
5531 TIM_ITRx_SetConfig(htim->Instance, TIM_CLOCKSOURCE_TI1);
5532 break;
5533 }
5534
5535 case TIM_CLOCKSOURCE_TI2:
5536 {
5537 /* Check whether or not the timer instance supports external clock mode 1 (ETRF)*/
5538 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLOCKSOURCE_TIX_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
5539
5540 /* Check TI2 input conditioning related parameters */
5541 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLOCKPOLARITY(sClockSourceConfig->ClockPolarity));
5542 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLOCKFILTER(sClockSourceConfig->ClockFilter));
5543
5544 TIM_TI2_ConfigInputStage(htim->Instance,
5545 sClockSourceConfig->ClockPolarity,
5546 sClockSourceConfig->ClockFilter);
5547 TIM_ITRx_SetConfig(htim->Instance, TIM_CLOCKSOURCE_TI2);
5548 break;
5549 }
5550
5551 case TIM_CLOCKSOURCE_TI1ED:
5552 {
5553 /* Check whether or not the timer instance supports external clock mode 1 */
5554 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLOCKSOURCE_TIX_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
5555
5556 /* Check TI1 input conditioning related parameters */
5557 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLOCKPOLARITY(sClockSourceConfig->ClockPolarity));
5558 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLOCKFILTER(sClockSourceConfig->ClockFilter));
5559
5560 TIM_TI1_ConfigInputStage(htim->Instance,
5561 sClockSourceConfig->ClockPolarity,
5562 sClockSourceConfig->ClockFilter);
5563 TIM_ITRx_SetConfig(htim->Instance, TIM_CLOCKSOURCE_TI1ED);
5564 break;
5565 }
5566
5567 case TIM_CLOCKSOURCE_ITR0:
5568 case TIM_CLOCKSOURCE_ITR1:
5569 case TIM_CLOCKSOURCE_ITR2:
5570 case TIM_CLOCKSOURCE_ITR3:
5571 {
5572 /* Check whether or not the timer instance supports internal trigger input */
5573 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLOCKSOURCE_ITRX_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
5574
5575 TIM_ITRx_SetConfig(htim->Instance, sClockSourceConfig->ClockSource);
5576 break;
5577 }
5578
5579 default:
5580 status = HAL_ERROR;
5581 break;
5582 }
5583 htim->State = HAL_TIM_STATE_READY;
5584
5585 __HAL_UNLOCK(htim);
5586
5587 return status;
5588}
5589
5602HAL_StatusTypeDef HAL_TIM_ConfigTI1Input(TIM_HandleTypeDef *htim, uint32_t TI1_Selection)
5603{
5604 uint32_t tmpcr2;
5605
5606 /* Check the parameters */
5607 assert_param(IS_TIM_XOR_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
5608 assert_param(IS_TIM_TI1SELECTION(TI1_Selection));
5609
5610 /* Get the TIMx CR2 register value */
5611 tmpcr2 = htim->Instance->CR2;
5612
5613 /* Reset the TI1 selection */
5614 tmpcr2 &= ~TIM_CR2_TI1S;
5615
5616 /* Set the TI1 selection */
5617 tmpcr2 |= TI1_Selection;
5618
5619 /* Write to TIMxCR2 */
5620 htim->Instance->CR2 = tmpcr2;
5621
5622 return HAL_OK;
5623}

5634HAL_StatusTypeDef HAL_TIM_SlaveConfigSynchro(TIM_HandleTypeDef *htim, TIM_SlaveConfigTypeDef *sSlaveConfig)
5635{
5636 /* Check the parameters */
5637 assert_param(IS_TIM_SLAVE_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
5638 assert_param(IS_TIM_SLAVE_MODE(sSlaveConfig->SlaveMode));
5639 assert_param(IS_TIM_TRIGGER_SELECTION(sSlaveConfig->InputTrigger));
5640
5641 __HAL_LOCK(htim);
5642
5643 htim->State = HAL_TIM_STATE_BUSY;
5644
5645 if (TIM_SlaveTimer_SetConfig(htim, sSlaveConfig) != HAL_OK)
5646 {
5647 htim->State = HAL_TIM_STATE_READY;
5648 __HAL_UNLOCK(htim);
5649 return HAL_ERROR;
5650 }
5651
5652 /* Disable Trigger Interrupt */
5653 __HAL_TIM_DISABLE_IT(htim, TIM_IT_TRIGGER);
5654
5655 /* Disable Trigger DMA request */
5656 __HAL_TIM_DISABLE_DMA(htim, TIM_DMA_TRIGGER);
5657
5658 htim->State = HAL_TIM_STATE_READY;
5659
5660 __HAL_UNLOCK(htim);
5661
5662 return HAL_OK;
5663}

5674HAL_StatusTypeDef HAL_TIM_SlaveConfigSynchro_IT(TIM_HandleTypeDef *htim,
5675 TIM_SlaveConfigTypeDef *sSlaveConfig)
5676{
5677 /* Check the parameters */

5680 assert_param(IS_TIM_TRIGGER_SELECTION(sSlaveConfig->InputTrigger));

5683
5684 htim->State = HAL_TIM_STATE_BUSY;
5685
5686 if (TIM_SlaveTimer_SetConfig(htim, sSlaveConfig) != HAL_OK)
5687 {
5688 htim->State = HAL_TIM_STATE_READY;
5689 __HAL_UNLOCK(htim);
5690 return HAL_ERROR;
5691 }
5692
5693 /* Enable Trigger Interrupt */
5694 __HAL_TIM_ENABLE_IT(htim, TIM_IT_TRIGGER);
5695
5696 /* Disable Trigger DMA request */
5697 __HAL_TIM_DISABLE_DMA(htim, TIM_DMA_TRIGGER);
5698
5699 htim->State = HAL_TIM_STATE_READY;
5700
5701 __HAL_UNLOCK(htim);
5702
5703 return HAL_OK;
5704}

5772

6607
6625void TIM_DMAError(DMA_HandleTypeDef *hdma)
6626{
6627 TIM_HandleTypeDef *htim = (TIM_HandleTypeDef *)((DMA_HandleTypeDef *)hdma)->Parent;
6628
6629 if (hdma == htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC1])
6630 {
6631 htim->Channel = HAL_TIM_ACTIVE_CHANNEL_1;
6632 TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_1, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY);
6633 }
6634 else if (hdma == htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC2])
6635 {
6636 htim->Channel = HAL_TIM_ACTIVE_CHANNEL_2;
6637 TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_2, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY);
6638 }
6639 else if (hdma == htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC3])
6640 {
6641 htim->Channel = HAL_TIM_ACTIVE_CHANNEL_3;
6642 TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_3, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY);
6643 }
6644 else if (hdma == htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC4])
6645 {
6646 htim->Channel = HAL_TIM_ACTIVE_CHANNEL_4;
6647 TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_4, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY);
6648 }
6649 else
6650 {
6651 htim->State = HAL_TIM_STATE_READY;
6652 }
6653
6654#if (USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS == 1)
6655 htim->ErrorCallback(htim);
6656#else
6657 HAL_TIM_ErrorCallback(htim);
6658#endif /* USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS */
6659
6660 htim->Channel = HAL_TIM_ACTIVE_CHANNEL_CLEARED;
6661}
6662
6668static void TIM_DMADelayPulseCplt(DMA_HandleTypeDef *hdma)
6669{
6670 TIM_HandleTypeDef *htim = (TIM_HandleTypeDef *)((DMA_HandleTypeDef *)hdma)->Parent;
6671
6672 if (hdma == htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC1])
6673 {
6674 htim->Channel = HAL_TIM_ACTIVE_CHANNEL_1;
6675
6676 if (hdma->Init.Mode == DMA_NORMAL)
6677 {
6678 TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_1, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY);
6679 }
6680 }
6681 else if (hdma == htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC2])
6682 {
6683 htim->Channel = HAL_TIM_ACTIVE_CHANNEL_2;
6684
6685 if (hdma->Init.Mode == DMA_NORMAL)
6686 {
6687 TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_2, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY);
6688 }
6689 }
6690 else if (hdma == htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC3])
6691 {
6692 htim->Channel = HAL_TIM_ACTIVE_CHANNEL_3;
6693
6694 if (hdma->Init.Mode == DMA_NORMAL)
6695 {
6696 TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_3, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY);
6697 }
6698 }
6699 else if (hdma == htim->hdma[TIM_DMA_ID_CC4])
6700 {
6701 htim->Channel = HAL_TIM_ACTIVE_CHANNEL_4;
6702
6703 if (hdma->Init.Mode == DMA_NORMAL)
6704 {
6705 TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_SET(htim, TIM_CHANNEL_4, HAL_TIM_CHANNEL_STATE_READY);
6706 }
6707 }
6708 else
6709 {
6710 /* nothing to do */
6711 }
6712
6713#if (USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS == 1)
6714 htim->PWM_PulseFinishedCallback(htim);
6715#else
6716 HAL_TIM_PWM_PulseFinishedCallback(htim);
6717#endif /* USE_HAL_TIM_REGISTER_CALLBACKS */
6718
6719 htim->Channel = HAL_TIM_ACTIVE_CHANNEL_CLEARED;
6720}

6936
6943void TIM_Base_SetConfig(TIM_TypeDef *TIMx, TIM_Base_InitTypeDef *Structure)
6944{
6945 uint32_t tmpcr1;
6946 tmpcr1 = TIMx->CR1;
6947
6948 /* Set TIM Time Base Unit parameters ---------------------------------------*/
6949 if (IS_TIM_COUNTER_MODE_SELECT_INSTANCE(TIMx))
6950 {
6951 /* Select the Counter Mode */
6952 tmpcr1 &= ~(TIM_CR1_DIR | TIM_CR1_CMS);
6953 tmpcr1 |= Structure->CounterMode;
6954 }
6955
6956 if (IS_TIM_CLOCK_DIVISION_INSTANCE(TIMx))
6957 {
6958 /* Set the clock division */
6959 tmpcr1 &= ~TIM_CR1_CKD;
6960 tmpcr1 |= (uint32_t)Structure->ClockDivision;
6961 }
6962
6963 /* Set the auto-reload preload */
6964 MODIFY_REG(tmpcr1, TIM_CR1_ARPE, Structure->AutoReloadPreload);
6965
6966 TIMx->CR1 = tmpcr1;
6967
6968 /* Set the Autoreload value */
6969 TIMx->ARR = (uint32_t)Structure->Period ;
6970
6971 /* Set the Prescaler value */
6972 TIMx->PSC = Structure->Prescaler;
6973
6974 if (IS_TIM_REPETITION_COUNTER_INSTANCE(TIMx))
6975 {
6976 /* Set the Repetition Counter value */
6977 TIMx->RCR = Structure->RepetitionCounter;
6978 }
6979
6980 /* Generate an update event to reload the Prescaler
6981 and the repetition counter (only for advanced timer) value immediately */
6982 TIMx->EGR = TIM_EGR_UG;
6983}
6984
6991static void TIM_OC1_SetConfig(TIM_TypeDef *TIMx, TIM_OC_InitTypeDef *OC_Config)
6992{
6993 uint32_t tmpccmrx;
6994 uint32_t tmpccer;
6995 uint32_t tmpcr2;
6996
6997 /* Disable the Channel 1: Reset the CC1E Bit */
6998 TIMx->CCER &= ~TIM_CCER_CC1E;
6999
7000 /* Get the TIMx CCER register value */
7001 tmpccer = TIMx->CCER;
7002 /* Get the TIMx CR2 register value */
7003 tmpcr2 = TIMx->CR2;
7004
7005 /* Get the TIMx CCMR1 register value */
7006 tmpccmrx = TIMx->CCMR1;
7007
7008 /* Reset the Output Compare Mode Bits */
7009 tmpccmrx &= ~TIM_CCMR1_OC1M;
7010 tmpccmrx &= ~TIM_CCMR1_CC1S;
7011 /* Select the Output Compare Mode */
7012 tmpccmrx |= OC_Config->OCMode;
7013
7014 /* Reset the Output Polarity level */
7015 tmpccer &= ~TIM_CCER_CC1P;
7016 /* Set the Output Compare Polarity */
7017 tmpccer |= OC_Config->OCPolarity;
7018
7019 if (IS_TIM_CCXN_INSTANCE(TIMx, TIM_CHANNEL_1))
7020 {
7021 /* Check parameters */
7022 assert_param(IS_TIM_OCN_POLARITY(OC_Config->OCNPolarity));
7023
7024 /* Reset the Output N Polarity level */
7025 tmpccer &= ~TIM_CCER_CC1NP;
7026 /* Set the Output N Polarity */
7027 tmpccer |= OC_Config->OCNPolarity;
7028 /* Reset the Output N State */
7029 tmpccer &= ~TIM_CCER_CC1NE;
7030 }
7031
7032 if (IS_TIM_BREAK_INSTANCE(TIMx))
7033 {
7034 /* Check parameters */
7035 assert_param(IS_TIM_OCNIDLE_STATE(OC_Config->OCNIdleState));
7036 assert_param(IS_TIM_OCIDLE_STATE(OC_Config->OCIdleState));
7037
7038 /* Reset the Output Compare and Output Compare N IDLE State */
7039 tmpcr2 &= ~TIM_CR2_OIS1;
7040 tmpcr2 &= ~TIM_CR2_OIS1N;
7041 /* Set the Output Idle state */
7042 tmpcr2 |= OC_Config->OCIdleState;
7043 /* Set the Output N Idle state */
7044 tmpcr2 |= OC_Config->OCNIdleState;
7045 }
7046
7047 /* Write to TIMx CR2 */
7048 TIMx->CR2 = tmpcr2;
7049
7050 /* Write to TIMx CCMR1 */
7051 TIMx->CCMR1 = tmpccmrx;
7052
7053 /* Set the Capture Compare Register value */
7054 TIMx->CCR1 = OC_Config->Pulse;
7055
7056 /* Write to TIMx CCER */
7057 TIMx->CCER = tmpccer;
7058}
7059
7066void TIM_OC2_SetConfig(TIM_TypeDef *TIMx, TIM_OC_InitTypeDef *OC_Config)
7067{
7068 uint32_t tmpccmrx;
7069 uint32_t tmpccer;
7070 uint32_t tmpcr2;
7071
7072 /* Disable the Channel 2: Reset the CC2E Bit */
7073 TIMx->CCER &= ~TIM_CCER_CC2E;
7074
7075 /* Get the TIMx CCER register value */
7076 tmpccer = TIMx->CCER;
7077 /* Get the TIMx CR2 register value */
7078 tmpcr2 = TIMx->CR2;
7079
7080 /* Get the TIMx CCMR1 register value */
7081 tmpccmrx = TIMx->CCMR1;
7082
7083 /* Reset the Output Compare mode and Capture/Compare selection Bits */
7084 tmpccmrx &= ~TIM_CCMR1_OC2M;
7085 tmpccmrx &= ~TIM_CCMR1_CC2S;
7086
7087 /* Select the Output Compare Mode */
7088 tmpccmrx |= (OC_Config->OCMode << 8U);
7089
7090 /* Reset the Output Polarity level */
7091 tmpccer &= ~TIM_CCER_CC2P;
7092 /* Set the Output Compare Polarity */
7093 tmpccer |= (OC_Config->OCPolarity << 4U);
7094
7095 if (IS_TIM_CCXN_INSTANCE(TIMx, TIM_CHANNEL_2))
7096 {
7097 assert_param(IS_TIM_OCN_POLARITY(OC_Config->OCNPolarity));
7098
7099 /* Reset the Output N Polarity level */
7100 tmpccer &= ~TIM_CCER_CC2NP;
7101 /* Set the Output N Polarity */
7102 tmpccer |= (OC_Config->OCNPolarity << 4U);
7103 /* Reset the Output N State */
7104 tmpccer &= ~TIM_CCER_CC2NE;
7105
7106 }
7107
7108 if (IS_TIM_BREAK_INSTANCE(TIMx))
7109 {
7110 /* Check parameters */
7111 assert_param(IS_TIM_OCNIDLE_STATE(OC_Config->OCNIdleState));
7112 assert_param(IS_TIM_OCIDLE_STATE(OC_Config->OCIdleState));
7113
7114 /* Reset the Output Compare and Output Compare N IDLE State */
7115 tmpcr2 &= ~TIM_CR2_OIS2;
7116 tmpcr2 &= ~TIM_CR2_OIS2N;
7117 /* Set the Output Idle state */
7118 tmpcr2 |= (OC_Config->OCIdleState << 2U);
7119 /* Set the Output N Idle state */
7120 tmpcr2 |= (OC_Config->OCNIdleState << 2U);
7121 }
7122
7123 /* Write to TIMx CR2 */
7124 TIMx->CR2 = tmpcr2;
7125
7126 /* Write to TIMx CCMR1 */
7127 TIMx->CCMR1 = tmpccmrx;
7128
7129 /* Set the Capture Compare Register value */
7130 TIMx->CCR2 = OC_Config->Pulse;
7131
7132 /* Write to TIMx CCER */
7133 TIMx->CCER = tmpccer;
7134}

7376
7383static HAL_StatusTypeDef TIM_SlaveTimer_SetConfig(TIM_HandleTypeDef *htim,
7384 TIM_SlaveConfigTypeDef *sSlaveConfig)
7385{
7386 HAL_StatusTypeDef status = HAL_OK;
7387 uint32_t tmpsmcr;
7388 uint32_t tmpccmr1;
7389 uint32_t tmpccer;
7390
7391 /* Get the TIMx SMCR register value */
7392 tmpsmcr = htim->Instance->SMCR;
7393
7394 /* Reset the Trigger Selection Bits */
7395 tmpsmcr &= ~TIM_SMCR_TS;
7396 /* Set the Input Trigger source */
7397 tmpsmcr |= sSlaveConfig->InputTrigger;
7398
7399 /* Reset the slave mode Bits */
7400 tmpsmcr &= ~TIM_SMCR_SMS;
7401 /* Set the slave mode */
7402 tmpsmcr |= sSlaveConfig->SlaveMode;
7403
7404 /* Write to TIMx SMCR */
7405 htim->Instance->SMCR = tmpsmcr;
7406
7407 /* Configure the trigger prescaler, filter, and polarity */
7408 switch (sSlaveConfig->InputTrigger)
7409 {
7410 case TIM_TS_ETRF:
7411 {
7412 /* Check the parameters */
7413 assert_param(IS_TIM_CLOCKSOURCE_ETRMODE1_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
7414 assert_param(IS_TIM_TRIGGERPRESCALER(sSlaveConfig->TriggerPrescaler));
7415 assert_param(IS_TIM_TRIGGERPOLARITY(sSlaveConfig->TriggerPolarity));
7416 assert_param(IS_TIM_TRIGGERFILTER(sSlaveConfig->TriggerFilter));
7417 /* Configure the ETR Trigger source */
7418 TIM_ETR_SetConfig(htim->Instance,
7419 sSlaveConfig->TriggerPrescaler,
7420 sSlaveConfig->TriggerPolarity,
7421 sSlaveConfig->TriggerFilter);
7422 break;
7423 }
7424
7425 case TIM_TS_TI1F_ED:
7426 {
7427 /* Check the parameters */
7428 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC1_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
7429 assert_param(IS_TIM_TRIGGERFILTER(sSlaveConfig->TriggerFilter));
7430
7431 if (sSlaveConfig->SlaveMode == TIM_SLAVEMODE_GATED)
7432 {
7433 return HAL_ERROR;
7434 }
7435
7436 /* Disable the Channel 1: Reset the CC1E Bit */
7437 tmpccer = htim->Instance->CCER;
7438 htim->Instance->CCER &= ~TIM_CCER_CC1E;
7439 tmpccmr1 = htim->Instance->CCMR1;
7440
7441 /* Set the filter */
7442 tmpccmr1 &= ~TIM_CCMR1_IC1F;
7443 tmpccmr1 |= ((sSlaveConfig->TriggerFilter) << 4U);
7444
7445 /* Write to TIMx CCMR1 and CCER registers */
7446 htim->Instance->CCMR1 = tmpccmr1;
7447 htim->Instance->CCER = tmpccer;
7448 break;
7449 }
7450
7451 case TIM_TS_TI1FP1:
7452 {
7453 /* Check the parameters */
7454 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC1_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
7455 assert_param(IS_TIM_TRIGGERPOLARITY(sSlaveConfig->TriggerPolarity));
7456 assert_param(IS_TIM_TRIGGERFILTER(sSlaveConfig->TriggerFilter));
7457
7458 /* Configure TI1 Filter and Polarity */
7459 TIM_TI1_ConfigInputStage(htim->Instance,
7460 sSlaveConfig->TriggerPolarity,
7461 sSlaveConfig->TriggerFilter);
7462 break;
7463 }
7464
7465 case TIM_TS_TI2FP2:
7466 {
7467 /* Check the parameters */
7468 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC2_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
7469 assert_param(IS_TIM_TRIGGERPOLARITY(sSlaveConfig->TriggerPolarity));
7470 assert_param(IS_TIM_TRIGGERFILTER(sSlaveConfig->TriggerFilter));
7471
7472 /* Configure TI2 Filter and Polarity */
7473 TIM_TI2_ConfigInputStage(htim->Instance,
7474 sSlaveConfig->TriggerPolarity,
7475 sSlaveConfig->TriggerFilter);
7476 break;
7477 }
7478
7479 case TIM_TS_ITR0:
7480 case TIM_TS_ITR1:
7481 case TIM_TS_ITR2:
7482 case TIM_TS_ITR3:
7483 {
7484 /* Check the parameter */
7485 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC2_INSTANCE(htim->Instance));
7486 break;
7487 }
7488
7489 default:
7490 status = HAL_ERROR;
7491 break;
7492 }
7493
7494 return status;
7495}
7496
7517void TIM_TI1_SetConfig(TIM_TypeDef *TIMx, uint32_t TIM_ICPolarity, uint32_t TIM_ICSelection,
7518 uint32_t TIM_ICFilter)
7519{
7520 uint32_t tmpccmr1;
7521 uint32_t tmpccer;
7522
7523 /* Disable the Channel 1: Reset the CC1E Bit */
7524 TIMx->CCER &= ~TIM_CCER_CC1E;
7525 tmpccmr1 = TIMx->CCMR1;
7526 tmpccer = TIMx->CCER;
7527
7528 /* Select the Input */
7529 if (IS_TIM_CC2_INSTANCE(TIMx) != RESET)
7530 {
7531 tmpccmr1 &= ~TIM_CCMR1_CC1S;
7532 tmpccmr1 |= TIM_ICSelection;
7533 }
7534 else
7535 {
7536 tmpccmr1 |= TIM_CCMR1_CC1S_0;
7537 }
7538
7539 /* Set the filter */
7540 tmpccmr1 &= ~TIM_CCMR1_IC1F;
7541 tmpccmr1 |= ((TIM_ICFilter << 4U) & TIM_CCMR1_IC1F);
7542
7543 /* Select the Polarity and set the CC1E Bit */
7544 tmpccer &= ~(TIM_CCER_CC1P | TIM_CCER_CC1NP);
7545 tmpccer |= (TIM_ICPolarity & (TIM_CCER_CC1P | TIM_CCER_CC1NP));
7546
7547 /* Write to TIMx CCMR1 and CCER registers */
7548 TIMx->CCMR1 = tmpccmr1;
7549 TIMx->CCER = tmpccer;
7550}
7551
7564static void TIM_TI1_ConfigInputStage(TIM_TypeDef *TIMx, uint32_t TIM_ICPolarity, uint32_t TIM_ICFilter)
7565{
7566 uint32_t tmpccmr1;
7567 uint32_t tmpccer;
7568
7569 /* Disable the Channel 1: Reset the CC1E Bit */
7570 tmpccer = TIMx->CCER;
7571 TIMx->CCER &= ~TIM_CCER_CC1E;
7572 tmpccmr1 = TIMx->CCMR1;
7573
7574 /* Set the filter */
7575 tmpccmr1 &= ~TIM_CCMR1_IC1F;
7576 tmpccmr1 |= (TIM_ICFilter << 4U);
7577
7578 /* Select the Polarity and set the CC1E Bit */
7579 tmpccer &= ~(TIM_CCER_CC1P | TIM_CCER_CC1NP);
7580 tmpccer |= TIM_ICPolarity;
7581
7582 /* Write to TIMx CCMR1 and CCER registers */
7583 TIMx->CCMR1 = tmpccmr1;
7584 TIMx->CCER = tmpccer;
7585}

7607static void TIM_TI2_SetConfig(TIM_TypeDef *TIMx, uint32_t TIM_ICPolarity, uint32_t TIM_ICSelection,
7608 uint32_t TIM_ICFilter)
7609{
7610 uint32_t tmpccmr1;
7611 uint32_t tmpccer;
7612
7613 /* Disable the Channel 2: Reset the CC2E Bit */
7614 TIMx->CCER &= ~TIM_CCER_CC2E;
7615 tmpccmr1 = TIMx->CCMR1;
7616 tmpccer = TIMx->CCER;
7617
7618 /* Select the Input */
7619 tmpccmr1 &= ~TIM_CCMR1_CC2S;
7620 tmpccmr1 |= (TIM_ICSelection << 8U);
7621
7622 /* Set the filter */
7623 tmpccmr1 &= ~TIM_CCMR1_IC2F;
7624 tmpccmr1 |= ((TIM_ICFilter << 12U) & TIM_CCMR1_IC2F);
7625
7626 /* Select the Polarity and set the CC2E Bit */
7627 tmpccer &= ~(TIM_CCER_CC2P | TIM_CCER_CC2NP);
7628 tmpccer |= ((TIM_ICPolarity << 4U) & (TIM_CCER_CC2P | TIM_CCER_CC2NP));
7629
7630 /* Write to TIMx CCMR1 and CCER registers */
7631 TIMx->CCMR1 = tmpccmr1 ;
7632 TIMx->CCER = tmpccer;
7633}

7647static void TIM_TI2_ConfigInputStage(TIM_TypeDef *TIMx, uint32_t TIM_ICPolarity, uint32_t TIM_ICFilter)
7648{
7649 uint32_t tmpccmr1;
7650 uint32_t tmpccer;
7651
7652 /* Disable the Channel 2: Reset the CC2E Bit */
7653 TIMx->CCER &= ~TIM_CCER_CC2E;
7654 tmpccmr1 = TIMx->CCMR1;
7655 tmpccer = TIMx->CCER;
7656
7657 /* Set the filter */
7658 tmpccmr1 &= ~TIM_CCMR1_IC2F;
7659 tmpccmr1 |= (TIM_ICFilter << 12U);
7660
7661 /* Select the Polarity and set the CC2E Bit */
7662 tmpccer &= ~(TIM_CCER_CC2P | TIM_CCER_CC2NP);
7663 tmpccer |= (TIM_ICPolarity << 4U);
7664
7665 /* Write to TIMx CCMR1 and CCER registers */
7666 TIMx->CCMR1 = tmpccmr1 ;
7667 TIMx->CCER = tmpccer;
7668}

7690static void TIM_TI3_SetConfig(TIM_TypeDef *TIMx, uint32_t TIM_ICPolarity, uint32_t TIM_ICSelection,
7691 uint32_t TIM_ICFilter)
7692{
7693 uint32_t tmpccmr2;
7694 uint32_t tmpccer;
7695
7696 /* Disable the Channel 3: Reset the CC3E Bit */
7697 TIMx->CCER &= ~TIM_CCER_CC3E;
7698 tmpccmr2 = TIMx->CCMR2;
7699 tmpccer = TIMx->CCER;
7700
7701 /* Select the Input */
7702 tmpccmr2 &= ~TIM_CCMR2_CC3S;
7703 tmpccmr2 |= TIM_ICSelection;
7704
7705 /* Set the filter */
7706 tmpccmr2 &= ~TIM_CCMR2_IC3F;
7707 tmpccmr2 |= ((TIM_ICFilter << 4U) & TIM_CCMR2_IC3F);
7708
7709 /* Select the Polarity and set the CC3E Bit */
7710 tmpccer &= ~(TIM_CCER_CC3P | TIM_CCER_CC3NP);
7711 tmpccer |= ((TIM_ICPolarity << 8U) & (TIM_CCER_CC3P | TIM_CCER_CC3NP));
7712

7781static void TIM_ITRx_SetConfig(TIM_TypeDef *TIMx, uint32_t InputTriggerSource)
7782{
7783 uint32_t tmpsmcr;
7784
7785 /* Get the TIMx SMCR register value */
7786 tmpsmcr = TIMx->SMCR;
7787 /* Reset the TS Bits */
7788 tmpsmcr &= ~TIM_SMCR_TS;
7789 /* Set the Input Trigger source and the slave mode*/
7790 tmpsmcr |= (InputTriggerSource | TIM_SLAVEMODE_EXTERNAL1);
7791 /* Write to TIMx SMCR */
7792 TIMx->SMCR = tmpsmcr;
7793}
7811void TIM_ETR_SetConfig(TIM_TypeDef *TIMx, uint32_t TIM_ExtTRGPrescaler,
7812 uint32_t TIM_ExtTRGPolarity, uint32_t ExtTRGFilter)
7813{
7814 uint32_t tmpsmcr;
7815
7816 tmpsmcr = TIMx->SMCR;
7817
7818 /* Reset the ETR Bits */
7819 tmpsmcr &= ~(TIM_SMCR_ETF | TIM_SMCR_ETPS | TIM_SMCR_ECE | TIM_SMCR_ETP);
7820
7821 /* Set the Prescaler, the Filter value and the Polarity */
7822 tmpsmcr |= (uint32_t)(TIM_ExtTRGPrescaler | (TIM_ExtTRGPolarity | (ExtTRGFilter << 8U)));
7823
7824 /* Write to TIMx SMCR */
7825 TIMx->SMCR = tmpsmcr;
7826}
7827
7843void TIM_CCxChannelCmd(TIM_TypeDef *TIMx, uint32_t Channel, uint32_t ChannelState)
7844{
7845 uint32_t tmp;
7846
7847 /* Check the parameters */
7848 assert_param(IS_TIM_CC1_INSTANCE(TIMx));
7849 assert_param(IS_TIM_CHANNELS(Channel));
7850
7851 tmp = TIM_CCER_CC1E << (Channel & 0x1FU); /* 0x1FU = 31 bits max shift */
7852
7853 /* Reset the CCxE Bit */
7854 TIMx->CCER &= ~tmp;
7855
7856 /* Set or reset the CCxE Bit */
7857 TIMx->CCER |= (uint32_t)(ChannelState << (Channel & 0x1FU)); /* 0x1FU = 31 bits max shift */
7858}
